  <div class="single-journal-entry-wrapper">
    


<div class="journal-entry-wrapper post-text authored-by-ohhowcivilized ">
<div id="item32323822" class="journal-entry">

  <div class="journal-entry-float-day"><span class="name">Friday</span></div><div class="journal-entry-float-date"><span class="month">Jan</span><span class="date">04</span><span class="year">2013</span></div>
  
  
  
  <div class="journal-entry-text">
  
      
      <h2 class="title">
    
        
    
        <a class="journal-entry-navigation-current" href="/blog/2013/1/4/the-j-crew-sleeve-roll.html">The J. Crew Sleeve&nbsp;Roll</a>  
     
         
    
      </h2>
      
       <div class="journal-entry-tag journal-entry-tag-post-title"><span class="posted-on">   <img title="Date" alt="Date" class="inline-icon date-icon" rel="smalllight" src="/universal/images/transparent.png" />Friday, January 4, 2013</span> </div> 

    
  
      
      <div class="body">
  
        
        
        
          <p><span class="full-image-block ssNonEditable"><img src="/storage/post-images/jcrew_sleeve_roll_1_0113.jpg?__SQUARESPACE_CACHEVERSION=1357266034903" alt="" /></span></p>
<p>On Fridays, I'll be sharing a tip that you may find useful. It's something you may <em>not know,</em> but you may <em>want to know.</em> To kick things off, here's the J. Crew Sleeve Roll. This is how they roll the sleeves on the button downs and it's what you're taught when you first start working there.&nbsp;</p>
<p><em style="font-size: 80%;">Photo Credit: Queenie Fok</em></p>

        
  
          
  
         
  
